definitions.definition: The person or thing in the third position .
One of three equal parts of a whole.
examples: He ate a third of the pie. Divided by two- thirds .

definitions.definition: The third gear of a gearbox .
An interval consisting of the first and third notes in a scale .

examples: The play ended with Jones standing on third .

definitions.definition: A handicap of one stroke every third hole .
A third-class degree , awarded to the lowest achievers in an honours degree programme
One sixtieth of a second , i.e., the third in a series of fractional parts in a sexagesimal number system.

main_definition: The person or thing in the third position .
